).containsExactly(CharSequence.class);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsPublicAndDeclaredConstructors() {\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = scanMethodFixtures()) {\n            final ClassInfo classInfo = scanResult.getClassInfo(MethodFixtures.class.getName());\n            final MethodInfoList constructors = classInfo.getDeclaredConstructorInfo();\n\n            final MethodInfo publicConstructorInfo = constructorWithDescriptor(\n                    constructors, \"(Ljava/lang/String;)V\");\n            final MethodInfo privateConstructorInfo = constructorWithDescriptor(\n                    constructors, \"(J)V\");\n            final Constructor<?> publicConstructor = publicConstructorInfo\n                    .loadClassAndGetConstructor();\n            final Constructor<?> privateConstructor = privateConstructorInfo\n                    .loadClassAndGetConstructor();\n\n            assertThat(publicConstructor.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(MethodFixtures.class);\n            assertThat(publicConstructor.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(String.class);\n            assertThat(privateConstructor.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(MethodFixtures.class);\n            assertThat(privateConstructor.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(long.class);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static ScanResult scanMethodFixtures() {\n        return new ClassGraph()\n                .acceptClasses(MethodFixtures.class.getName())\n                .enableClassInfo()\n                .enableMethodInfo()\n                .ignoreMethodVisibility()\n                .scan();\n    }\n\n    private static MethodInfo constructorWithDescriptor(final MethodInfoList constructors,\n            final String descriptor) {\n        for (final MethodInfo constructor : constructors) {\n            if (descriptor.equals(constructor.getTypeDescriptorStr())) {\n                return constructor;\n            }\n        }\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"Constructor not found w